Stage and commit your files: Run the following commands to add all your files and create your first commit.

git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit of Next.js app"
Create a new repository on GitHub: Go to github.com and create a new, empty repository. Do not initialize it with a README, .gitignore, or a license.

Connect your local repository to GitHub: GitHub will provide you with the exact commands to link your local project to the new remote repository. It will typically look like this:

git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/your-repository-name.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main